# GitHub workflow (Lattice)

## Use `gh`, not the web UI

GitHub state in this repo is **config-as-code** under [`.github/`](.github/) — labels, milestones, epic + task issues, Project v2 fields, branch protection. UI clicks drift away on the next script run.

For every GitHub operation, follow the [`github-operations`](~/.cursor/skills/github-operations/SKILL.md) skill. The canonical entry points:

- **Labels** — edit `.github/labels.yml`, run `node .github/scripts/sync-labels.mjs`.
- **Milestones** — edit `.github/milestones.yml`, run `node .github/scripts/sync-milestones.mjs`.
- **Project v2 / issues** — edit `.github/issues/*.yml`, run `node .github/scripts/bootstrap-issues.mjs`.
- **Repo settings + branch protection** — edit `.github/scripts/bootstrap-repo.mjs`, run with `--apply-protection`.

See [`docs/development/github-governance.md`](docs/development/github-governance.md) for the full playbook.

## Commit + branch conventions

- Branch: `<type>/<short-slug>` — e.g. `feat/wiki-link-autocomplete`, `fix/graph-crash` ([CONTRIBUTING.md](CONTRIBUTING.md)).
- Commits + PR titles: [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/) ([ADR-0009](docs/decisions/0009-conventional-commits-trunk-based.md)).
- Merge strategy: **squash only**; PR title becomes the commit subject.

## PR template

Use a HEREDOC for the body — never paste multi-line markdown into a flag value:

```bash
gh pr create --draft --title "feat(area): one-line subject" --body "$(cat <<'EOF'
## Summary
- One bullet per behaviour change.

## Test plan
- [ ] What you ran locally.
- [ ] What CI will verify.

Closes #123
EOF
)"
```

## Branch protection is load-bearing

`main` requires (re-applied in v0.1 PR #11): `ci / meta`, `ci / frontend (ubuntu-latest|windows-latest)`, `ci / rust (ubuntu-latest|windows-latest)`, `ci / desktop-build (ubuntu-latest|windows-latest)`, `commitlint`. **Never** `gh pr merge --admin` or `git push --force origin main`.
